TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {38845=2012 Season (Sophomore): Named All-Northern Athletics Conference Second Team as a punter...Earned NAC Special Teams Player of the Week honors for Sept. 24-30...Took over the starting punting duties and appeared in nine games...Finished first in the Northern Athletics Conference with 1,988 yards punted, a NAC-best 13 punts inside the 20 yardline and tied for first in the NAC with 10 punt fair caught...Ranked second in the NAC with 54 punts and a 36.8 average (92nd in the nation)...Boomed seven punts for 318 yards (45.4 average), including a career-high 65 yarder at Augsburg College (Sept. 1)...Pinned two punts inside the 20 yardline, which were fair caught, on six punts against Trine University (Sept. 15)...Punted a career-high 10 times at Benedictine University (Sept. 29)...Punted twice inside the 20 yardline for 91 yards (45.5 average, a career-best) against Concordia University Chicago (Oct. 13)...Finished with seven punts for 251 yards (35.9 average), including two inside the 20 yardline at Lakeland College (Oct. 20)...Ended the season with six punts, two inside the 20 yardline and career-best four fair caught against Wisconsin Lutheran College (Nov. 10)., 40105=2011 Season (Freshman): Played primarily for the Falcons as a kicker and punter on the junior varisty team...Participated on the varsity team in the same capacity., 201133=CONCORDIA UNIVERSITY WISCONSIN ATHLETICS 12800 NORTH LAKE SHORE DRIVE MEQUON, WI 53097, 38370=2013 Season (Junior): Named Second Team All-Northern Athletics Collegiate Conference...Appeared in all 11 games...Averaged 37.6 yards per punt...Punted 35 times for 1,315 yards...Finished with 10 punts inside the 20-yard line...Boomed a career-long punt of 74 yards against Wisconsin Lutheran College (November 16)...Punted five times for 241 yards (48.2 yards per punt) against Augsburg College (September 7).}
